cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.DL

This paper deals with the practical implementation and evaluation of a smart contract-based PKI system using blockchain technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of distributed systems and fault tolerance, which suggests the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the second most likely. The paper also involves the implementation and evaluation of smart contracts, which falls under the category cs.SE (Software Engineering). The use of blockchain technology and its security implications suggest the category cs.CY (Computers and Society) as a likely category. Finally, the paper also discusses the computational complexity and storage requirements of the proposed system, which falls under the category cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
